The life cycle of Chinchero is brought full circle inChapter 7, Llacta/Community, and in the Epilogue thatfollows.AnoverviewofthechangesthatoccurredatthesiteafterTopa Incasdeathtellsarobusttaleofbetrayaland political maneuverings that quickly led to a familysplit, a difficult succession in rulers, and the imprisonmentofasonatChinchero.Asinmanycasesthroughoutthe New World, Spanish occupation of the estate led torepurposing of its buildings and open spaces and toneglectofothers.Anewlyimposed viceregal town planpermanentlyalteredthedesignandconfigurationofTopaIncas estate. The chapter speaks to the resilience andtenacity of its indigenous inhabitants over time and thefuture challenges they face.
